  "response": "Currently, there are no active-duty five-star generals in the United States military. The last five-star generals were appointed during and shortly after World War II. The most recent five-star generals were:\n\n1. Army: Omar Bradley (last five-star general, promoted in 1950)\n2. Air Force: Henry \"Hap\" Arnold\n3. Navy: William Halsey Jr. and Chester Nimitz\n\nDuring wartime, Congress can authorize the rank of General of the Army (Army) or Fleet Admiral (Navy), which are five-star ranks. However, no such promotions have been made since the mid-20th century. The highest active-duty rank today is four-star general or admiral.",
